{"title_page": "List of Academy Award Best Actress winners by age", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n[[File:Oscar-academy-award-free.png|thumb|A silhouette of the Oscar trophy]]\nThis is a list of winners of the [[Academy Award]] for [[Academy Award for Best Actress|Performance by an Actress in a Leading Role]], presented annually by the [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] (AMPAS)<ref>[http://www.oscars.org/ Official website of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]</ref> to an [[actress]] who has delivered an outstanding performance while working within the [[film industry]]. More popularly known as the [[Academy Award for Best Actress|Academy Award (or the Oscar) for Best Actress]], this award was initially presented at the [[1st Academy Awards]] ceremony for [[1927 in film|1927]]\u2013[[1928 in film|1928]] and was most recently presented at the [[92nd Academy Awards]] ceremony for [[2019 in film|2019]].<ref>[http://www.oscar.com/ Official ceremony promotional website for the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]</ref>  Throughout the past 92 years, accounting for ties and repeat winners, AMPAS has presented a total of 93 Best Actress awards to 77 different actresses. This list is current as of the [[92nd Academy Awards]] ceremony held on February 9, 2020.<ref>[http://www.oscars.org/awardsdatabase/index.html Official database website of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080913120840/http://www.oscars.org/awardsdatabase/index.html |date=2008-09-13 }}</ref>\n\n==List of winners==\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|-\n!align=\"center\"| #<br>\n!align=\"center\"| Actress<br/>\n!align=\"center\"| Film<br/>\n!align=\"center\"| Date of birth<br/>\n!align=\"center\" class=\"unsortable\" valign=\"top\"| Date of award<br/>\n!align=\"center\"| Age upon <br/>receiving award<br/>\n!align=\"center\"| Date of death<br/>\n!align=\"center\"| Lifespan<br/>\n!align=\"center\" class=\"unsortable\" valign=\"top\"| Notes<br/>\n|- style=\"text-align: left; background:#FFFFFF\"\n| 1\n| <span style=\"display:none\">Gaynor, Janet</span>[[Janet Gaynor]]\n| <span style=\"display:none\">Seventh Heaven, Street Angel and Sunrise: A Song of Two Humans</span>''[[7th Heaven (1927 film)|7th Heaven]]'',<br>''[[Street Angel (1928 film)|Street Angel]]'', and ''[[Sunrise: A Song of Two Humans]]''\n| <span style=\"display:none\">1906-10-06</span>{{birth date|1906|10|6}}\n| {{Start date|1929|5|16}}\n| {{ayd|1906|10|6|1929|5|16}}\n| <span style=\"display:none\">1984-09-14</span>{{Death date|1984|9|14}}\n| {{formatnum:{{age in days|1906|10|6|1984|9|14}}}} days ({{ayd|1906|10|6|1984|9|14}})\n| Held record as youngest winner for 59 award ceremonies (from the 1st to the 59th, May 1929\u2013March 1987 [57 years, 10 months])\n|- style=\"text-align: left; background:#FFFFFF\"\n| 2\n| <span style=\"display:none\">Pickford, Mary</span>[[Mary Pickford]]\n| <span style=\"display:none\">Coquette</span>''[[Coquette (film)|Coquette]]''\n| <span style=\"display:none\">1892-04-08</span>{{birth date|1892|4|8}}\n| {{Start date|1930|4|3}}\n| {{ayd|1892|4|8|1930|4|3}}\n| <span style=\"display:none\">1979-05-29</span>{{Death date|1979|5|29}}\n| {{formatnum:{{age in days|1892|4|8|1979|5|29}}}} days ({{ayd|1892|4|8|1979|5|29}})\n| Held record as oldest winner for 2 award ceremonies (from the 2nd to the 4th, April 1930\u2013November 1931 [1 year, 7 months])\n|- style=\"text-align: left; background:#FFFFFF\"\n| 3\n| <span style=\"display:none\">Shearer, Norma</span>[[Norma Shearer]]\n| <span style=\"display:none\">Divorcee</span>''[[The Divorcee]]''\n| <span style=\"display:none\">1902-08-10</span>{{birth date|1902|8|10}}\n| {{Start date|1930|11|5}}\n| {{ayd|1902|8|10|1930|11|5}}\n| <span style=\"display:none\">1983-06-12</span>{{Death date|1983|6|12}}\n| {{formatnum:{{age in days|1902|8|10|1983|6|12}}}} days ({{ayd|1902|8|10|1983|6|12}})\n|\n|- style=\"text-align: left; back