website)|The Numbers]]|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Misbehaviour''''' is a 2020 British [[comedy-drama]] film directed by [[Philippa Lowthorpe]], from a screenplay by [[Gaby Chiappe]] and [[Rebecca Frayn]], from a story by Frayn. The film stars [[Keira Knightley]], [[Gugu Mbatha-Raw]], [[Jessie Buckley]], [[Keeley Hawes]], [[Phyllis Logan]], [[Lesley Manville]], [[Rhys Ifans]] and [[Greg Kinnear]].\n\n''Misbehaviour'' was released in the United Kingdom on 13 March 2020 by [[Path\u00e9]]'s distribution partner [[20th Century Fox]].\n\n==Premise==\nThe film follows the events of the [[Miss World 1970|1970 Miss World competition]], which saw the crowning of the first black competitor.\n\n==Cast==\n{{cast list|\n* [[Keira Knightley]] as [[Sally Alexander]]\n* [[Gugu Mbatha-Raw]] as [[Jennifer Hosten]], [[Miss Grenada World|Miss Grenada]]\n* [[Jessie Buckley]] as Jo Robinson\n* [[Lesley Manville]] as [[Dolores Hope]]\n* [[Greg Kinnear]] as [[Bob Hope]]\n* [[Keeley Hawes]] as [[Julia Morley]]\n* [[Rhys Ifans]] as [[Eric Morley]]\n* [[Phyllis Logan]] as Evelyn Alexander\n* [[John Sackville (actor)|John Sackville]] as [[Robin Day]]\n* [[Suki Waterhouse]] as Sandra Wolsfeld - [[United States representatives at Miss World|Miss United States]]\n* Clara Rosager as Marjorie Johansson - [[Miss World Sweden|Miss Sweden]]\n* Loreece Harrison as Pearl Jansen - [[Miss Africa South]]\n* Emma Corrin as Jillian Jessup - [[Miss South Africa]]\n* [[Misato Omori]] as Hisayo Nakamura - [[Miss Japan]]\n* Collet Collins as Jennifer Wong - [[Miss Guyana]]\n* Emily Tebbutt as Yvonne Ormes - [[Miss United Kingdom]]\n* Monica Sarup as Heather Faville - [[Femina Miss India|Miss India]]\n* [[Delly Allen]] as [[Georgina Rizk]] - [[Miss Lebanon]]\n* Taina Haines as S\u00f4nia Guerra - [[Miss Brazil World|Miss Brazil]]\n* Lily Newmark as Jane\n* Emma D'Arcy as Hazel\n* [[Ruby Bentall]] as Sarah\n* [[Alexa Davies]] as Sue\n* [[John Heffernan (actor)|John Heffernan]] as [[Gareth Stedman Jones]]\n* Maya Kelly as [[Abigail Thaw]]\n* [[Eileen O\u2019Higgins]] as Joan Billings\n* [[Miles Jupp]] as Clive \n* [[Charlotte Spencer (actress)|Charlotte Spencer]] as TV girl\n* Charlie Anson as [[Michael Aspel]]\n}}\n\n==Production==\nThe film was announced in October 2018, with [[Keira Knightley]], [[Gugu Mbatha-Raw]] and [[Jessie Buckley]] set to star. [[Philippa Lowthorpe]] was set to direct.<ref>[https://deadline.com/2018/10/keira-knightley-gugu-mbatha-raw-jessie-buckley-the-crown-misbehaviour-1202484446/ Keira Knightley, Gugu Mbatha-Raw & Jessie Buckley To Star In Miss World Film \u2018Misbehaviour\u2019 For Left Bank & Path\u00e9 \u2014 AFM]</ref> In November 2018, [[Lesley Manville]], [[Greg Kinnear]],  [[Keeley Hawes]], [[Rhys Ifans]] and [[Phyllis Logan]] had joined the cast of the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/keira-knightley-misbehaviour-greg-kinnear-lesley-manville-keeley-hawes-miss-world-1202508636/|title=\u2018Misbehaviour\u2019: Greg Kinnear & Lesley Manville To Play Bob & Dolores Hope In Keira Knightley Miss World Movie|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Andreas|last=Wiseman|date=26 November 2018|accessdate=26 November 2018}}</ref> In September 2018 Collet Collins joined the cast, and in January 2019 [[Suki Waterhouse]] and Clara Rosager joined.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/suki-waterhouse-keira-knightley-miss-world-misbehaviour-the-crown-1202531258/|title=Suki Waterhouse To Play Miss USA In Keira Knightley-Fronted Miss World Movie \u2018Misbehaviour\u2019|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Andreas|last=Wiseman|date=8 January 2019|accessdate=8 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/clara-rosager-keira-knightley-miss-world-movie-misbehaviour-1202531886/|title=Scandi Actress Clara Rosager To Play Miss Sweden In Keira Knightley Pageant Protest Movie \u2018Misbehaviour\u2019|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Andreas|last=Wiseman|date=9 January 2019|accessdate=9 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\n[[Principal photography]] began in November 2018. Filming in the Crofton Park area of South East London occurred in early January 2019 <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.screendaily.com/news/lesley-manville-greg-kinnear-keeley-hawes-join-pathe-left-bank-project-misbehaviour-/5134770.article|title=Lesley Manville, Greg Kinnear, Keeley Hawes join Path\u00e9, Left Bank project 'Misbehaviour'|website=[[Screen International]]|first=Orlando|last=Parfitt|date=26 November 2018|accessdate=26 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe film was released in the United Kingdom on 13 March 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/12/misbehaviour-trailer-keira-knightley-gugu-mbatha-raw-miss-world-1202813553/|title=\u2018Misbehaviour\u2019 Trailer: Keira Knightley & Gugu Mbatha-Raw Star In Comedy-Drama About 1970 Miss World Comp|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Andreas|last=Wiseman|date=19 December 2019|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref> [[Shout Factory|Shout Studios]] will distribute in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/shout-studios-misbehaviour-keira-knightley-gugu-mbatha-raw-1202884335/|title=Shout! Studios Lands Pageant Drama \u2018Misbehaviour\u2019 Starring Keira Knightley & Gugu Mbatha-Raw|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=16 March 2020|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref> Due to the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]] the film will be released through [[video on demand]] in the United Kingdom on 15 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/04/keira-knightley-starrer-misbehaviour-uk-ireland-film-releases-heading-online-early-due-to-coronavirus-disruption-1202901336/|title=Keira Knightley Starrer \u2018Misbehaviour\u2019 \u2013 UK & Ireland Film Releases Heading Online Early Due To Coronavirus Disruption|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Tom|last=Grater|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n{{As of|2020|3|18|df=UK}}, ''Misbehaviour'' has grossed the equivalent of $426,765 in the United Kingdom.<ref name=\"BOM\"/><ref name=\"NUM\"/>\n\n===Critical response===\nOn the [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 88% based on 25 reviews, with an average rating of 6.45/10. The site's critics consensus reads: \"''Misbehaviour''{{'}}s overall arc will be familiar to fans of feelgood British cinema \u2013 and so will the way it triumphs over formula to tell a thoroughly crowd-pleasing story.\"<ref name=\"rottentomatoes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/misbehaviour|title=Misbehaviour (2020)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango]]|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|9148706}}\n\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:British films]]\n[[Category:British comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Path\u00e9 films]]\n[[Category:BBC Films films]]\n[[Category:20th Century Fox films]]\n[[Category:Beauty pageant films]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 1970s]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1970]]\n[[Category:British films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:Miss World 1970]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the British film|the South Korean film|Misbehavior (film)}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Misbehaviour\n| image          = Misbehaviour poster.jpg\n| border         = no\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Philippa Lowthorpe]]\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Suzanne Mackie\n* Sarah-Jane Wheale\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{plainlist|\n* [[Gaby Chiappe]]\n* [[Rebecca Frayn]]\n}}\n| story          = Rebecca Frayn\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Keira Knightley]]\n* [[Gugu Mbatha-Raw]]\n* [[Jessie Buckley]]\n* [[Keeley Hawes]]\n* [[Phyllis Logan]]\n* [[Lesley Manville]]\n* [[Rhys Ifans]]\n* [[Greg Kinnear]]\n}}<!--PER POSTER BILLING BLOCK-->\n| music          = [[Dickon Hinchliffe]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Dickon Hinchliffe Scoring Philippa Lowthorpe\u2019